m_north.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/US23_cut_at_Pound_Gap.jpg/1280px-US23_cut_at_Pound_Gap.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c2/US23_cut_at_Pound_Gap.jpg","cap":"US23 cut at Pound Gap","desc":"Looking westward along U.S. Route 23 into the main cut atop Pound Gap , a mountain pass in the Cumberland Mountains of the United States . Photo is taken in Wise County , Virginia , while the more distant areas of the picture are part of Letcher County , Kentucky .","credit":"Nyttend · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:US23_cut_at_Pound_Gap.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Garred_Chapel_ruins.jpg/1280px-Garred_Chapel_ruins.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/ba/Garred_Chapel_ruins.jpg","cap":"Garred Chapel ruins","desc":"Roadside view of a largely destroyed building located on the southeastern side of U.S. Route 23 southwest of Louisa in Lawrence County , Kentucky , United States . Known as the Garred Chapel , it was built in 1870 for a Methodist congregation, and it is listed on the National Register of Historic Places .","credit":"Nyttend · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Garred_Chapel_ruins.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Crump_and_Field_Grocery_Company.jpg/1280px-Crump_and_Field_Grocery_Company.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/Crump_and_Field_Grocery_Company.jpg","cap":"Crump and Field Grocery Company","desc":"Front of the former Crump and Field Grocery Company , located at 1401-1405 Greenup Avenue (U.S. Routes 23 / 60 ) in Ashland , Kentucky , United States . Built in 1892, it is listed on the National Register of Historic Places .","credit":"Nyttend · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Crump_and_Field_Grocery_Company.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/c